which some famous actors used to wear.

92
00:06:38,829 --> 00:06:41,528
Mr. Nakagami has at least 40 hats.

93
00:06:41,529 --> 00:06:45,928
He wears them when he goes to the turf, just for good luck.

94
00:06:45,929 --> 00:06:50,328
Mr. Iwatomi was the victim's golf friend, had 30 pairs of white golf shoes.

95
00:06:50,329 --> 00:06:52,228
These are all expensive brand shoes.

96
00:06:52,229 --> 00:06:55,828
He polishes them all once a week.

97
00:06:55,829 --> 00:07:00,128
And lastly. The victim, President Tsujiya was obsessed with idols.

98
00:07:00,129 --> 00:07:02,928
It seems he had been collecting a lot of idol goods.

99
00:07:02,929 --> 00:07:08,628
I found a lot those idol goods in the president's room over there.

100
00:07:08,629 --> 00:07:11,128
That! See the one on the desk?

101
00:07:11,129 --> 00:07:15,028
Pens and pen stands with the idol's picture on them and stuff.

102
00:07:15,029 --> 00:07:16,229
I see.

103
00:07:18,129 --> 00:07:20,528
Hey, Kudo. Have you noticed it?

104
00:07:20,529 --> 00:07:23,628
You mean the unnaturalness of the desk?

105
00:07:23,629 --> 00:07:26,128
But it's not only that.

106
00:07:26,129 --> 00:07:30,128
Right. There's one more thing that's kind of bugging me.

107
00:07:30,129 --> 00:07:33,728
I suppose this calendar is also the president's stuff, right?

108
00:07:33,729 --> 00:07:37,628
Yes. That calendar is actually his favourite,

109
00:07:37,629 --> 00:07:40,829
so he kept it even after that month passed.

110
00:07:44,929 --> 00:07:46,229
Hattori.

111
00:07:47,729 --> 00:07:51,128
Did you buy it? The novel.

112
00:07:51,129 --> 00:07:54,428
My mom also got me one first thing in the morning today.

113
00:07:54,429 --> 00:07:57,328
Have you figured out something, Kazuha?

114
00:07:57,329 --> 00:07:58,728
Kazuha?

115
00:07:58,729 --> 00:08:01,528
Sorry, Ran. I can't talk right now.

116
00:08:01,529 --> 00:08:03,329
I think I'm just about to solve it.

117
00:08:06,829 --> 00:08:10,228
What is it now? What time do you think it is?

118
00:08:10,229 --> 00:08:13,728
Don't you tell me you are still suspicious about us?

119
00:08:13,729 --> 00:08:15,028
Well...

120
00:08:15,029 --> 00:08:19,428
I heard some money matters were involved in this murder.

121
00:08:19,429 --> 00:08:24,228
It's all because of our vague alibis. We have no proof as to it.

122
00:08:24,229 --> 00:08:27,628
But what can I do? I was really at the turf that day.

123
00:08:27,629 --> 00:08:31,928
I was at a golf course, watching the final round of the tournament.

124
00:08:31,929 --> 00:08:35,728
I was watching movies. Actually, three movies in a row.

125
00:08:35,729 --> 00:08:39,728
I was out fishing. I just happened to go by myself.

126
00:08:39,729 --> 00:08:40,729
All right.

127
00:08:40,730 --> 00:08:42,928
So who found the dead body first?

128
00:08:42,929 --> 00:08:44,228
Who is this boy?

129
00:08:44,229 --> 00:08:48,029
Could you just tell me more about it, please?

130
00:08:49,629 --> 00:08:52,628
It's me who found him first.

131
00:08:52,629 --> 00:08:56,428
I was going to sit at my desk when I found him lying on the floor.

132
00:08:56,429 --> 00:08:58,028
I screamed.

133
00:08:58,029 --> 00:09:00,028
As we heard Mr. Iwatomi's scream,

134
00:09:00,029 --> 00:09:03,528
we all came here and called the police.

135
00:09:03,529 --> 00:09:04,829
Right.

136
00:09:06,929 --> 00:09:10,628
Before I forget, is it your president who rips the pages off the calendar?

137
00:09:10,629 --> 00:09:15,228
Yes. The president gets upset if we do it because we might ruin it.

138
00:09:15,229 --> 00:09:17,428
So Mr. Tsujiya always rips it off.

139
00:09:17,429 --> 00:09:21,128
And he keeps it in his room like some kind of precious treasure.

140
00:09:21,129 --> 00:09:25,529
Was he also the one who wrote the schedule on the calendar?

141
00:09:26,729 --> 00:09:32,328
We were all supposed to play some golf together next Sunday.

142
00:09:32,329 --> 00:09:34,728
I can't believe this actually happened.

143
00:09:34,729 --> 00:09:38,928
Anyway, we've got to go to look for something.

144
00:09:38,929 --> 00:09:41,229
You guys do the talking, okay?

145
00:09:49,229 --> 00:09:51,628
All right. Let's do it.

146
00:09:51,629 --> 00:09:53,428
Yes.

147
00:09:53,429 --> 00:09:56,728
The fact the video camera was at a blind spot

148
00:09:56,729 --> 00:09:58,628
from the victim's point of view,

149
00:09:58,629 --> 00:10:01,228
and the unnaturally neat desk.

150
00:10:01,229 --> 00:10:05,828
The bloodstain on the leather coat the murderer was wearing.

151
00:10:05,829 --> 00:10:08,528
The suspects' strange obsessions.

152
00:10:08,529 --> 00:10:12,428
And the president's dying message.

153
00:10:12,429 --> 00:10:13,828
Right.

154
00:10:13,829 --> 00:10:16,528
Now, all we need is that thing.

155
00:10:16,529 --> 00:10:19,228
The thing that connects the pieces of the mystery all together.

156
00:10:19,229 --> 00:10:22,628
What? One of the suspects got a solid alibi?

157
00:10:22,629 --> 00:10:26,828
Yes. I'm at the TV station, checking the footage.

158
00:10:26,829 --> 00:10:28,328
I see him.

159
00:10:28,329 --> 00:10:29,729
Clearly.

160
00:10:32,229 --> 00:10:33,329
Kudo.

161
00:10:36,629 --> 00:10:37,829
Ran.

162
00:10:39,229 --> 00:10:40,528
I found it.

163
00:10:40,529 --> 00:10:42,528
It's the June calendar.

164
00:10:42,529 --> 00:10:46,028
There's a thin bloodstain, but I can still see it.

165
00:10:46,029 --> 00:10:47,428
That must be it.

166
00:10:47,429 --> 00:10:49,428
The murderer is...

167
00:10:49,429 --> 00:10:50,729
I got it.

168
00:10:51,929 --> 00:10:54,328
Ran, I think...

169
00:10:54,329 --> 00:10:56,229
I got the answer.

170
00:11:00,916 --> 00:11:03,715
Seriously? You really got the answer?

171
00:11:03,716 --> 00:11:08,315
The dying message the president left at the murder scene.

172
00:11:08,316 --> 00:11:12,215
Yes. The four building blocks with the ink spots, right?

173
00:11:12,216 --> 00:11:15,915
That looked like a hidden secret code,

174
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:18,915
but it was simply indicating the murderer.

175
00:11:18,916 --> 00:11:20,515
The murderer?

176
00:11:20,516 --> 00:11:24,515
I don't think there's any person that looks like a building block.

177
00:11:24,516 --> 00:11:26,415
No! It's the name.

178
00:11:26,416 --> 00:11:27,515
Name?

179
00:11:27,516 --> 00:11:30,715
None of the four names are related to "o", "mo", "chi", "ya" though.

180
00:11:30,716 --> 00:11:33,315
Heiji mentioned it earlier. Remember?

181
00:11:33,316 --> 00:11:35,815
The victim might have just put the blocks on the ink,

182
00:11:35,816 --> 00:11:39,115
and not because he wanted us to read what's with the ink spots.

183
00:11:39,116 --> 00:11:42,115
In other words, the backside of the ink spotted character

184
00:11:42,116 --> 00:11:44,615
is the true dying message.

185
00:11:44,616 --> 00:11:48,615
I understand. But we can't see what behind those characters.

186
00:11:48,616 --> 00:11:52,515
I can ask the forensic officers to bring them here.

187
00:11:52,516 --> 00:11:54,415
No, you don't have to do that.

188
00:11:54,416 --> 00:11:55,815
Look.

189
00:11:55,816 --> 00:11:58,815
The blocks of "o" character

190
00:11:58,816 --> 00:12:02,115
would look like this if I were to unfold it.

191
00:12:02,116 --> 00:12:04,315
U, e, o?

192
00:12:04,316 --> 00:12:08,215
You all know what kind of character will be in the blank space, right?

193
00:12:08,216 --> 00:12:11,915
Just in case, I checked the blocks over there.

194
00:12:11,916 --> 00:12:14,215
As I expected,

195
00:12:14,216 --> 00:12:19,415
the characters are lined up in the correct order.

196
00:12:19,416 --> 00:12:21,315
Ms. Aiko, am I right?

197
00:12:21,316 --> 00:12:25,115
Yes. Each block contains five characters with the same consonant

198
00:12:25,116 --> 00:12:29,116
and an animal picture in the same order.

199
00:12:31,316 --> 00:12:37,515
If you know which character is on which side, it is no longer a hustle.

200
00:12:37,516 --> 00:12:39,915
The backside of "o" is "i".

201
00:12:39,916 --> 00:12:44,415
Accordingly, "mo" is "mi" and "chi" is "to".

202
00:12:44,416 --> 00:12:48,815
Right! So the real dying message is "i", "mi", "to"...

203
00:12:48,816 --> 00:12:50,015
And what's the last one?

204
00:12:50,016 --> 00:12:51,615
It doesn't make sense.

205
00:12:51,616 --> 00:12:57,815
According to Kazuha, the last block "ya" is supposed to be "yu".

206
00:12:57,816 --> 00:13:00,115
But I actually see "yo" on it.

207
00:13:00,116 --> 00:13:02,615
That block is special.

208
00:13:02,616 --> 00:13:06,416
Look. You see "wo" on the right side of "yo"?

209
00:13:07,516 --> 00:13:12,415
That means this block consists of "ya", "yu", "yo", "wa", "wo" "n".

210
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:17,215
If we put those characters in the same order, the animal part will be "n".

211
00:13:17,216 --> 00:13:18,815
That's it!

212
00:13:18,816 --> 00:13:22,815
According to the same rule, "ya" is "wa".

213
00:13:22,816 --> 00:13:24,715
So the dying message is

214
00:13:24,716 --> 00:13:27,416
"i", "mi", "to", "wa", right?

215
00:13:28,616 --> 00:13:31,115
-So that's... -Imiwato.

216
00:13:31,116 --> 00:13:32,615
Iwamito...

217
00:13:32,616 --> 00:13:35,115
-Iwato. -Iwato.

218
00:13:35,116 --> 00:13:36,116
That's right.

219
00:13:36,117 --> 00:13:39,116
That's what the president wanted to tell us before he was killed.

220
00:13:41,116 --> 00:13:43,215
The vice-president, Mr. Iwatomi.

221
00:13:43,216 --> 00:13:45,315
It was your name.

222
00:13:45,316 --> 00:13:46,615
I see.

223
00:13:46,616 --> 00:13:50,615
You wanted to kill your president and take over the company, didn't you?

224
00:13:50,616 --> 00:13:52,215
No, I...

225
00:13:52,216 --> 00:13:53,815
Kazuha, that was amazing!

226
00:13:53,816 --> 00:13:56,115
You actually solve the case before Hattori.

227
00:13:56,116 --> 00:13:58,615
We won this deduction battle!

228
00:13:58,616 --> 00:14:00,015
So that means...

229
00:14:00,016 --> 00:14:03,315
We can go to the Takarazuka show.

230
00:14:03,316 --> 00:14:04,915
Sorry, Kazuha.

231
00:14:04,916 --> 00:14:06,816
Mr. Iwatomi is not the murderer.

232
00:14:08,516 --> 00:14:11,515
I had a phone call from Chiba.

233
00:14:11,516 --> 00:14:15,015
The 29th of last month around 5pm, when the murder occurred,

234
00:14:15,016 --> 00:14:17,515
Mr. Iwatomi was in fact on TV.

235
00:14:17,516 --> 00:14:19,515
-No way. -Why?

236
00:14:19,516 --> 00:14:22,115
Don't ask me why.

237
00:14:22,116 --> 00:14:23,915
You have a twin brother?

238
00:14:23,916 --> 00:14:25,116
No, I don't.

239
00:14:27,116 --> 00:14:32,115
Sorry to tell you this, but Kazuha's idea was wrong.

240
00:14:32,116 --> 00:14:33,116
Oh, no.

241
00:14:33,117 --> 00:14:36,016
No. She was right.

242
00:14:38,016 --> 00:14:40,315
The four blocks are really the dying message

243
00:14:40,316 --> 00:14:45,415
the president Tsujiya left before he was killed.

244
00:14:45,416 --> 00:14:46,815
Heiji.

245
00:14:46,816 --> 00:14:50,215
But Hattori, Mr. Iwatomi has an alibi.

246
00:14:50,216 --> 00:14:52,315
Of course he has an alibi.

247
00:14:52,316 --> 00:14:54,915
Because Mr. Iwatomi is not the murderer at all.

248
00:14:54,916 --> 00:14:56,615
What?

249
00:14:56,616 --> 00:15:01,215
You just said that it was the real dying message, didn't you?

250
00:15:01,216 --> 00:15:04,015
Yes. For sure, I did.

251
00:15:04,016 --> 00:15:07,715
But I didn't say the message was correct, did I?

252
00:15:07,716 --> 00:15:10,215
Hey, hey. What are you talking about?

253
00:15:10,216 --> 00:15:11,715
Hey, don't you remember?

254
00:15:11,716 --> 00:15:14,715
How did President Tsujiya leave a message on the blocks?

